<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Relations With DPRK Said Rated `First' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1003014894 Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN in Korean 10 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK1003014894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP report from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] Japan's KYODO news agency reports from Beijing on 9 
March that in the upcoming Chinese People's National Congress 
meeting, the government action report that Premier Li Peng will 
present is supposed to mention China's friendly relations with 
North Korea first in its foreign policy division, thereby 
stressing the complete restoration of North Korea-China 
relations. 
  KYODO reported this citing Chinese sources, and said that 
while China's top priority last year was on the development of 
Sino- Japanese relations, the order of priority has changed this 
year. 
  KYODO said that China will list North Korea-China friendly 
relations first on China's priority list in Premier Li Peng's 
foreign policy action report apparently to proclaim the complete 
restoration of Sino-North Korean relations which have cooled off 
since the establishment of Sino-ROK relations in August 1992. 

</TEXT>

