<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by Romanian Delegation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Trade Ministers Meet </H4>
<F P=102> SK1003020994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0038 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1003020994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 10 (YONHAP) -- Trade, Industry and 
Energy Minister Kim Chol-su and his Romanian counterpart 
Cristian Ionescu agreed Thursday to hold the first meeting of 
the Korea-Romania Joint Economic Committee as soon as possible. 
  In their meeting, Kim proposed that Romanian industries set 
up subsidiaries and stage goods fairs here while Ionescu, who is 
visiting with Romanian President Ion Iliescu, suggested that the 
two countries exchange trade delegations and private-sector 
visits in a bid to narrow the current trade imbalance. 
  Seoul sold goods worth 80 million U.S. dollars to Bucharest 
and imported products worth 6 million dollars to record a 
74-million-dollar surplus last year. 

</TEXT>

