<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by Romanian Delegation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Han Meets Counterpart; Signs Pact </H4>
<F P=102> SK1003084394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0816 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1003084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 10 (YONHAP) -- South Korean Foreign 
Minister Han Sung-chu met his visiting Romanian counterpart 
Teodor Melescanu Thursday and discussed the North Korean nuclear 
problem, international affairs and ways to boost bilateral 
economic cooperation. 
  Han sought Bucharest's support for Seoul's bid to become a 
non-permanent member of the United Nations Security Council in 
1996-1997, and Melescanu promised full cooperation, said Paek 
Nak-hwan, director-general of the Ministry's European affairs 
bureau. 
  The two foreign ministers also signed an aviation pact 
allowing Korean civilian airlines to fly freely to the Eastern 
European country. 

</TEXT>

