<H3> <TI>   Government To Seek Nonpermanent UN Council Seat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1003080694 Seoul YONHAP in English 0748 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1003080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, march 10 (YONHAP) -- South Korea has 
officially notified the United Nations of its intention to seek 
non-permanent membership in the U.N. Security Council, a 
government official said Thursday. 
  He said the government officially conveyed its intent last 
month to the Asia group, comprising 46 countries, to contest an 
election for non-permanent members of the Security Council next 
year at the U.N. General Assembly. 

</TEXT>

