<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK Official's Remarks on DPRK-U.S. Talks Decried </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1003142494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1305 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1003142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1305 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to Seoul Radio, on 9 March the South 
Korean puppet vice foreign minister made the absurd remark 
[tangchi anun chapsorirul chechyossumnida] that it is unclear if 
the third round of DPRK-U.S. talks will be held, mentioning the 
nuclear inspection and North-South dialogue. 
  As has already been reported, an International Atomic Energy 
Agency [IAEA] inspection team started inspections of us on 1 
March, according to an agreement reached in DPRK-U.S. contacts 
in New York, and our country's organizations concerned are 
cooperating in the inspection team's activities. 
  Our position is to sincerely implement agreements regarding 
the IAEA inspections to guarantee the continuity of nuclear 
safeguards. Despite this fact, the puppet vice foreign minister 
said that the agency's inspections of us are unsatisfactory. 
His remarks are indeed extremely absurd and preposterous. 
  The puppet vice foreign minister also said that the 
South-North dialogue is not going smoothly. If we have to say 
something about this, we can say that the South is entirely 
responsible for this. 
  In the fifth working-level contact for an exchange of 
special 
envoys of the North and South, the South side, instead of 
expressing a clear attitude toward our side's principled demand 
before discussing practical problems, made preposterous 
sophistries that our demand creates obstacles and that it is 
unnecessary, thus creating obstacles to the discussions of 
problems. 
  The South side even deliberately raised an issue that has no 
relation to the discussions of the practical procedure and 
blemished the atmosphere of the talks, assuming an extremely 
provocative attitude. 
  The puppets are now saying that the North-South dialogue is 
not going smoothly, after they themselves created deliberate 
obstacles to working-level contacts. This is no more than 
avoiding their responsibility. 
  Never should it go unnoticed that the puppets keep insisting 
that progress in North-South dialogue is a precondition for the 
third round of DPRK-U.S. talks. 
  As we have already elucidated, in the agreement reached at 
the DPRK-U.S. contact in New York, it only mentions the 
resumption of working-level contact for the exchange of special 
envoys of the North and South as one of the steps of 
simultaneous action [tongsi haengdong chochi]. There is no 
indication about the realization of the exchange of special 
envoys. 
  The two sides of the DPRK and U.S. did not agree to the 
steps 
of simultaneous action with something as a precondition. The 
reason that the puppets are continuously babbling about some a 
precondition is ultimately to create an artificial barrier to 
put the brakes on the third round of DPRK-U.S. talks. This is 
nothing but a nasty scheme. 
  This is being vividly proven by the fact that the so-called 
puppet vice foreign minister confessed that consultations are 
being continuously carried out with allies, including the United 
States, on the issue of referring the North Korean nuclear issue 
to the UN Security Council. 
  Under the pretext of dialogue, the Kim Yong-sam puppet 
clique 
is pursuing behind the scenes the anti-Republic maneuver of 
isolation and suffocation under the international cooperative 
system [kukche kongjo cheje]. This will ultimately only lead to 
the road of pressing for destruction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

