<F P=100> INTER-ASIAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Openness Toward Newly Liberalized Nations Urged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903080294 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0903080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Philippines has asked the Association of 
Southeast Nations, or ASEAN, to adopt a more open attitude 
toward newly liberalized countries in the region. These 
countries are Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar [Burma], and Vietnam. The 
call was made by the Philippine delegation to the special 
meeting of the ASEAN senior officials held recently in Bangkok. 
  Delegation head Foreign Affairs Undersecretary Rodolfo 
Severino called on ASEAN to eventually accept these newly 
industrialized [as heard] countries into the association. He 
said the inclusion of these four countries in ASEAN could 
prevent future conflicts and promote political stability and 
economic progress. 

</TEXT>

