<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Rejection" issued by the National Army of Democratic </F>
Kampuchea spokesman on 9 March -- place not given] 
  [Text] I. On 7 March, the Hanoi Vietnamese communists 
ordered their lackey puppets in the two-headed government to 
claim once again that the National Army of Democratic Kampuchea 
[NADK] had used Thai territory to defeat them on the Anlung Veng 
battlefield. This is a dirty and base accusation; no one except 
the notoriously cunning Vietnamese communists could think of 
playing the trick of the thief shouting: Stop thief! 
  II. For what purpose did the Vietnamese communists order 
their puppets to level this accusation? It was based on the 
following: 
  1. Covering their most shameful and severe defeat on the 
Anlung Veng battlefield. The Vietnamese communists and their 
alliance have claimed various unreasonable pretexts to fool 
their lackeys into further inflaming the war to serve their 
strategic policies. 
  2. Covering the shipment of Vietnamese forces and armaments 
to Cambodia in accordance with what the Vietnamese communists 
call Cambodian-Vietnamese military cooperation, which they 
agreed upon with the puppet Chea Sim in Hanoi in early March. 
The Vietnamese communists have painstakingly implemented the 
strategy and tactics of launching attacks in western Cambodia 
and shipping Vietnamese men and women to the eastern part of the 
country. 
  3. The Party of Democratic Kampuchea [PDK] and the NADK have 
always respected and will always respect the Kingdom of 
Thailand's sovereignty and territorial integrity. They have 
never done anything that affects the Royal Thai Government or 
the Thai people. The PDK and the entire Cambodian nation and 
people want to coexist peacefully with all neighboring 
countries, especially Thailand and the Thai people, who respect 
other countries' sovereignty and territorial integrity. The 
Thais are different from the Vietnamese communist puppets and 
the two-headed government, who -- relying on the Vietnamese 
communists and the Western alliance -- have implemented the 
policy of further inflaming the war, both inside and outside the 
country, and then denounced other people without any sense of 
responsibility. [Dated] 9 March 1994 [Signed] The NADK spokesman 

