<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Villagers Kill Government General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1003072694 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1003072694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 25 February, inhabitants at Ap Village in Kang 
Meas District of Kompong Cham Province intercepted a group of 
Vietnamese communist puppet troops led by some generals and 
senior officers, who were rounding up the people's husbands and 
children to serve as soldiers and die in their place. The 
people killed six of them, including a general and a senior 
officer. We also seized two pistols and four AK rifles. 
  And on 24 February, people and village guards ambushed a 
group of Vietnamese communist puppet troops from Chamka Leu 
District in Kompong Cham Province. The troops attempted to 
terrorize and massacre the people and plunder their property at 
Phkai Meas Village in the district. Four enemy soldiers were 
killed and eight wounded. We also seized a field radio and some 
documents. 

