<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suharto Meets With Cuban Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1003100794 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0600 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1003100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Suharto received a courtesy call from 
visiting Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina, who was 
accompanied by Foreign Minister Ali Alatas. During the 
occasion, Robaina conveyed Cuban President Fidel Castro's 
written message to President Suharto. 
  According to Alatas, the written message, among other 
things, 
clarified the itinerary of the minister's visit to Indonesia and 
other countries such as Vietnam, Laos, Cambodia and Malaysia. 
  During the meeting, Suharto briefed his guest on Indonesia's 
development program. On bilateral relations, Suharto said the 
Indonesian Government observes the principles of mutual respect 
of sovereignty, territorial integrity and non-interference in 
internal affairs. He said bilateral cooperation based on mutual 
benefit could be developed through a desirable manner. 
  Meanwhile, in his clarification to newsmen, Robaina said 
that 
cooperation between the two countries will be upgraded. As such, 
it would be necessary to study sectors which need to be 
developed. 
  Robaina said the Cuban Government was satisfied with 
Indonesia's leadership as chairman of the Nonaligned Movement. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

