<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   $8.5 Million Bridge Project for Cambodia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1003095894 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1003095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Australian Government has opened tenders for the 
rebuilding of up to 16 medium span bridges in Cambodia in an aid 
project worth $8.5 million [Australian dollars]. The project 
followed the construction of six bridges along Cambodia's 
national Route-5 from Phnom Penh to the border with Thailand. 
  The federal minister for development cooperation, Gordon 
Bilney, said the latest bridge project matches Australian 
engineering expertise with Cambodia's development priority. The 
bridge rebuilding is part of a nearly $17 million worth of 
development projects Australia is funding in Cambodia this year. 
  Mr. Bilney also announced the $600,000 grant for credit 
scheme in Cambodia aimed at helping people at the village level 
start small businesses and agricultural schemes. 

</TEXT>

