<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Papua New Guinea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Curfew Imposed in `Parts' of Northern Bougainville </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0803092294 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 8 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0803092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Renewed fighting between Papua New Guinea Government 
troops and Bougainville Revolutionary Army troops has led to the 
imposition of a curfew in parts of northern Bougainville. North 
Solomons Province Administrator Sam Tulo says the curfew comes 
following the murder of a police officer last week and an 
incident during which two rebels were shot dead. Mr. Tulo says 
all the attacks took place in northern Bougainville where rebels 
have stepped up action, particularly around the Wakunai 
government station. He says the situation is also tense in 
central Bougainville, where clashes between rebels and 
government troops have resulted in the death of one man and the 
wounding of four others. 

</TEXT>

