<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa Denies Knowledge of Ozawa's U.S. Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1103114194 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 10 Mar 93 
Evening Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1103114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ichiro Ozawa, general secretary of Shinseito [Japan 
Renewal Party], is reportedly preparing to visit the United 
States to break an impasse in the Japan-U.S. relations. Asked 
by a group of reporters about Mr. Ozawa's visit to Washington at 
the prime minister's official residence on 10 March, Prime 
Minister Hosokawa said: "I have not heard of it at all." Asked 
by a reporter if he has ever discussed the issue with Mr. Ozawa, 
the prime minister said: "I have not discussed it with him. 
When I inquired of each ministry and agency about his reported 
visit to Washington, all of them said they did not know about 
his visit to the United States." 

