<H3> <TI>   Hungarian Economic Minister Kadar Arrives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0503204294 Budapest MTI in English 1854 GMT 5 Mar 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0503204294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 5 (MTI) -- Hungarian Minister of 
International Economic Relations Bela Kadar arrived in Japan 
today to attend a session of the Japanese-U.S. committee set up 
to promote the Central European countries' economic development 
on Monday and Tuesday. 
  Subsequently, Kadar will hold talks in the Ministries of 
Foreign Affairs, International Trade and Industry. 
  The discussions are expected to focus on Hungary's admission 
to the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development and 
the related Japanese support. 
  Set up in 1989, the Japanese-U.S. committee regularly 
analyzes recent changes in the Visegrad countries (Czech 
Republic, Hungary, Poland, Slovakia) and reviews how Japan and 
the United States can help them catch up with the advanced 
industrial nations. 

</TEXT>

