<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prosecutors Arrest Former Construction Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1103132994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0754 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1103132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 11 KYODO -- Prosecutors arrested 
former Construction Minister Kishiro Nakamura Friday [11 March] 
on suspicion of taking a 10 million yen bribe from leading 
contractor Kajima Corp. 
  He is the first Diet member to be arrested in a widening 
scandal involving the construction industry. 
  The arrest of the former senior member of the main 
opposition 
Liberal Democratic Party came after the House of Representatives 
agreed earlier in the day to lift his parliamentary immunity. 
  Legislators cannot be arrested while the Diet is in session 
unless parliament gives its approval. 
  Nakamura surrendered himself to the Tokyo District 
Prosecutors office. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

