<H3> <TI>   Industrial Sector Cooperation Sought With Italy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0403143794 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1228 GMT 4 
Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0403143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Italy, Indonesia Seek Industrial </F>
Cooperation"] 
  [Excerpt] Jakarta, 4 Mar (ANSA) -- Privatizing Italian 
companies in the IRI [Institute for Industrial Reconstruction] 
group and their counterparts in Indonesia's state industrial 
sector are looking at possible avenues of cooperation, said 
IRI's international affairs director Alessandro Ovi, in Jakarta 
for a meeting with the Indonesian science and technology 
minister Habibie in the company of Italy's ambassador Mario 
Brando Penso. 
  The meeting, focusing on IRI's international objectives and 
on the industrial holding's interest in greater 
Italian-Indonesian cooperation, was followed by another with the 
Minister for Industry and Trade Hartarto, during a seminar 
organized by the Indonesian Agency for Strategic Industries 
(BPIS), attended by representatives of Finmeccanica [Mechanical 
Engineering Finance Corporation], Ansalfo, Alenia, Italtel and 
Elsag Bailey, all of the IRI group, as well as by 
representatives of BPIS companies and the relevant government 
ministries. [passage omitted] 

