<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ozawa Misses Hosokawa's Policy Speech to Diet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0503115094 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> OW0503115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shinseito Secretary General Ichiro Ozawa failed to 
attend the 4 March plenary session of the House of 
Representatives at which Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa 
delivered his policy speech. 
  Commenting on his nonattendance, a spokesman at Ozawa's 
office said: "He does not have any special plans. But he may 
be feeling a little fatigued." 
  However, as Mr. Ozawa is not known for missing plenary Diet 
sessions, the rumor has started that his absence was a silent 
protest against the prime minister's failure to reshuffle the 
cabinet. 
  Mr. Ozawa missed a meeting of the government and ruling 
party 
leaders held on the night of 2 March, at which the prime 
minister announced his decision to postpone a cabinet reshuffle. 
Since then, Mr. Ozawa has made no appearances at the Diet where 
he has previously appeared regularly. 
  A senior Shinseito staff member said: "He is not exactly 
dissatisfied with the prime minister, but rather irritated by 
the fact the political outlook has become uncertain. Although 
he may not make an appearance for about a week, he will show up 
sooner or later." 

</TEXT>

