<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Town Assembly Protests Fuel Leakage at Kadena </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1303083794 Naha OKINAWA TIMES in Japanese 11 Mar 94 
Evening Edition p 9 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1303083794 </F>
<F P=104>  Naha OKINAWA TIMES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kadena -- Following the leakage of jet fuel from 
Kadena Air Base [KAB], Kadena Town Assembly (chaired by Eiji 
Miyahira) unanimously adopted a "resolution to protest against 
the accident" at the beginning of a regular session which began 
on the afternoon of 11 March. Moreover, the resolution 
"protests with a sense of fury" against the U.S. military, the 
Defense Facilities Agency, and other government agencies, urging 
them to "take all possible measures to prevent similar accidents 
from happening again." 
  Nine members of the same town assembly's Special Committee 
for Base Affairs (chaired by Morisada Inamine) visited the KAB 
on 9 March and inspected the site of the accident. 
  The resolution strongly criticizes the U.S. military, 
saying: 
"Strong and foul smells enveloped the entire area, and the 
highly flammable material provoked fear among the residents. 
The anger of the townspeople has reached its outer limit. 
Accidents frequently occurred following the 1967 incident 
dubbed the "flammable well" and... These are the consequences 
of careless base management, which ignores the well-being of the 
residents." 
  Members of the town assembly plan to visit relevant 
organizations to file a protest in early April following the end 
of the regular session in March. 

</TEXT>

