<H3> <TI>   French Business Leader on Bilateral Ties Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1203074494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 11 Mar 
94 Morning Edition p 9 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1203074494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Japan-France Commission Joint Chairman Henri Martre 
(honorary chairman of Aerospatiale Co.), who is now on a visit 
to Japan to attend a general meeting of the Japan-France Club, 
granted an interview to a NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN reporter in Tokyo 
on 10 March. In the interview, he stressed: "France-Japan 
cooperation in settling the issue concerning the reconstruction 
of Cambodia is a good example of cooperation between the two 
countries. On the Bosnia-Herzegovina issue, it is possible for 
the two countries to make joint efforts to settle the ethnic 
strife there." In addition, he said: "In the tripolar structure 
among European nations, Japan, and the United States, 
strengthening relations between European nations and Japan is 
urgently needed." 
  Regarding the United States' reinstatement of the Super 301 
provision of the Omnibus Trade Act (sanctions measures against 
unfair trade partners), he expressed concern over the U.S. move, 
saying: "The United States' attitude is very much like someone 
sitting at a negotiating table on trade issues with a gun at 
their side." 
  The Japan-France Commission plans to submit to Prime 
Ministers Hosokawa and Balladur in the near future a report 
discussing relations between Japan and France in the long-term. 
He said the report will include a statement saying "it is 
important to improve bilateral economic relations." 

</TEXT>

