<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Hata Not To Meet With Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503113494 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 15 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 5 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1503113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata will visit Russia 
for two days from 20 to 21 March taking advantage of consecutive 
holidays. It was confirmed on 14 March, however, that Hata will 
not meet with President Yeltsin because he will take a two-week 
leave and will not stay in Moscow during Hata's visit to Moscow. 
The primary objective of the foreign minister's visit to Russia 
is to ask the president to reaffirm the "Tokyo Declaration" on 
which both Japan and Russia agreed last October and to express 
Japan's intention to continue its assistance for Russia's 
reforms. The foreign minister is not hiding his embarrassment at 
this development. 

</TEXT>

